The paper proposes a novel global localization method for robotics applications, which suggests that it belongs to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The method employs map traversability as a hidden observation, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of other sensors to boost localization performance, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of GPU for real-time performance, which involves systems and control (cs.SY) techniques.
